Lithuania has become more prosperous in recent years and funerals are usually arranged to follow recognised religious formulae. Religious services are usually held both before and after internment and may take an hour or more with religious services lasting up to three hours.

The Lithuanian Orthodox Church demands eight days of prayer in observance of rights before burial can take place. After religious services have been observed, posts are placed in the ground at both head and feet of the casket. These posts will only be removed on the day of the funeral.

Funerals are rather similar to that which the English adhere to with respect to burial proceedings, with the funeral proceeding on foot to the graveyard and the casket being lowered into the ground. Regular interment takes place as per rights but a mass can be held at the grave. Li
